726874f-b.text:
Hoffman Drive, south side, between Fifty-eighth and Fiftyninth Avenues, showing in three views tho Rohirson house. This house stands on or near the site of the Quaker Meeting House which was erected in 1722 and sold in 1760. Adjoinig the house Nas a burial ground. The house which was used as a dvelling from 1760 was consumed by fire in 1844. The owners of the present house were Robert kack, 18527; J. Robinson, 1850; Rohirson, 1891;
and possibly Mrs. Howard in 1873.
July 1923.
